703661f-a.text:
Clinton Street, east side, from, but not including Joralemon, to, but not including Schermerhorn Streets. On the right, is shown St. Ann's Episcopal Church. The view is taken north from Schermerhorn Street.
June 1, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.

705162f-a.text:
170 Joralemon Street, south side, from, including and across excavation on the east side of Clinton Street. The view shows Packer Collegiate
Institute.
February 22, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.

703660f-a.text:
Clinton Street, north from Joralemon Street, showing a 5 1/2-story building
at the S.W. corner, under construction or improvement.
March 27, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
703660f-a.folder: Clinton Street & Joralemon Street, Brooklyn, NY

703659f-b.text:
(1)
Clinton Street, east side, north from Joralemon Street. Also seen is 159-173 Joralemon Street, north side, east from Clinton Street. (The whhelock Home is at 161 Joralemon Street). The 10-story building at the left, belongs to the B.M.T Corp. Also seen at the left, is
the SpencetMemorial Presbyterian Church.
1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, showing a closer view of 161 Joralemon Street.
1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection,
(3)
The same, showing the N.E. corner now vacant, giving a clear view of
the church.
February 22, 1930.
L. Sperr.  NO REPRODUCTIONS.
